## 1. Product Identity

### What This Is
A **zero-manual-entry** personal finance system that ingests bank/UPI transaction emails from Gmail, parses them into structured data, and delivers actionable financial insights via a dashboard.

### What This Is NOT
- ❌ A manual expense tracker (Splitwise, Walnut)
- ❌ An AI-powered financial advisor (yet)
- ❌ A multi-bank aggregation platform (yet)

### Core Differentiator

| Dimension | Typical Apps | PFIS |
|-----------|-------------|------|
| Data Entry | Manual | **Fully automated** |
| Reports | Static | **Intelligent insights** |
| Visualization | Simple charts | **Behavioral analysis** |
| Data Sources | Single | **MCP-extensible** |

### Vision Statement
> *"A system that automatically understands your financial life and gives actionable decisions without any manual effort."*

### Four Pillars

| Pillar | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **Automation-first** | No typing — emails are the input |
| **Accuracy-first** | Correct parsing > fancy features |
| **Insight-driven** | Not just data → decisions |
| **Extensible** | Gmail today → multi-connectors tomorrow |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The entire value proposition collapses if parsing accuracy is poor. The parsing engine is the **single most critical component** — everything downstream depends on it.

