```

### Component Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    FE["Frontend Dashboard<br/>(Next.js)"] --> API["API Layer<br/>(REST)"]
    API --> GC["Gmail Connector"]
    API --> PE["Parsing Engine"]
    API --> PR["Processing Engine"]
    API --> IE["Insights Engine"]
    GC --> DB["PostgreSQL"]
    PE --> DB
    PR --> DB
    IE --> DB
    BW["Background Workers<br/>(BullMQ / Celery)"] --> GC
    BW --> PE
    BW --> PR
```

### Tech Stack (Prototype)

| Component | Choice | Rationale |
|-----------|--------|-----------|
| Backend | **Node.js** or **Python** | Node for speed-of-dev, Python for parsing strength |
| Database | **PostgreSQL** | Structured queries, JSON support, reliability |
| Queue | **BullMQ** (Node) / **Celery** (Python) | Async email processing |
| Frontend | **Next.js** | Dashboard with SSR |
| APIs | **REST** | Simple, sufficient for prototype |

> [!TIP]
> **My recommendation:** Use **Python (FastAPI)** for the backend. Email parsing is regex-heavy and Python's `re` module + NLP libraries (spaCy, dateutil) are significantly stronger than Node.js equivalents. Use BullMQ only if you go Node; otherwise Celery + Redis.

