## 3. Data Model Analysis

### Entity Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS ||--o{ GMAIL_ACCOUNTS : has
    USERS ||--o{ RAW_EMAILS : receives
    USERS ||--o{ TRANSACTIONS : owns
    USERS ||--o{ BUDGETS : sets
    RAW_EMAILS ||--o| TRANSACTIONS : generates
    TRANSACTIONS }o--|| CATEGORIES : belongs_to
    TRANSACTIONS }o--|| MERCHANTS : references
    CATEGORIES ||--o{ BUDGETS : limits
    MERCHANTS ||--o{ CATEGORIES : defaults_to

    USERS {
        uuid id PK
        string email
        string name
        string currency
        timestamp created_at
    }
    GMAIL_ACCOUNTS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        string google_account_id
        string access_token_ref
        string refresh_token_ref
        timestamp last_synced_at
    }
    RAW_EMAILS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        string gmail_message_id UK
        string subject
        text body
        string sender
        timestamp received_at
        boolean processed_flag
    }
    TRANSACTIONS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        decimal amount
        string currency
        enum transaction_type
        string merchant_raw
        string merchant_normalized
        uuid category_id FK
        date transaction_date
        string account_last4
        string reference_id
        float confidence_score
        uuid source_email_id FK
        timestamp created_at
    }
    CATEGORIES {
        uuid id PK
        string name
        uuid parent_category FK
        string icon
    }
    MERCHANTS {
        uuid id PK
        string normalized_name
        jsonb aliases
        uuid category_default FK
    }
    BUDGETS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        uuid category_id FK
        decimal monthly_limit
    }
```

### Key Design Decisions I've Identified

| Decision | Analysis |
|----------|----------|
| **Raw email storage** | ✅ Essential — enables re-parsing when rules improve |
| **Confidence score on transactions** | ✅ Critical — allows UI to flag low-confidence items for review |
| **Merchant normalization as separate table** | ✅ Smart — aliases JSON enables fuzzy matching |
| **`reference_id` on transactions** | ✅ Core to deduplication fingerprint |
| **`parent_category` self-reference** | ✅ Enables hierarchy (Food → Dining Out, Groceries) |

> [!WARNING]
> **Missing from the model:**
> - `sync_history` table — track each Gmail sync run (start, end, emails fetched, errors)
> - `parsing_rules` table — store versioned regex patterns for different banks
> - `audit_log` — track user corrections to improve parsing over time
> - `transaction_fingerprint` — a computed hash column for dedup (amount + date + merchant + ref_id)

