## 7. Security & Privacy

| Requirement | Implementation |
|------------|---------------|
| OAuth only | No password storage — Google OAuth 2.0 |
| Token encryption | Encrypt access/refresh tokens at rest (AES-256) |
| Minimal storage | Store only transaction-relevant email fields |
| Data masking | Mask account numbers: `XX1234` |
| Read-only access | Gmail scope: `gmail.readonly` |
| Disconnect | User can revoke access and delete data anytime |

> [!CAUTION]
> Store `access_token_ref` and `refresh_token_ref` as **references to a secrets manager** (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault), NOT as plaintext in the database.

---

## 8. Risk Assessment

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|------|----------|------------|
| Email format variability | 🔴 High | Bank-specific parser registry + generic fallback |
| Parsing errors (wrong amount) | 🔴 High | Confidence scoring + user review for low confidence |
| Duplicate transactions | 🟡 Medium | Fingerprint-based dedup with ref_id |
| Missing data fields | 🟡 Medium | Partial transactions stored with low confidence |
| Gmail API rate limits | 🟡 Medium | Exponential backoff + incremental sync |
| User trust erosion | 🔴 High | Show confidence, allow manual correction |
| Privacy concerns | 🔴 High | Read-only access, encryption, minimal storage |
| Bank template changes | 🟡 Medium | Versioned parser rules, monitoring for parse failures |

